Former President Olusegun Obasanjo has described Nigeria as a country presently dripping bitterness and sadness.  The former president argued that even though the country is destined to be a land flowing with milk and honey, bad leadership has made it unachievable.  He said this on Thursday while receiving a book titled, ‘The Man, The General and The President,’ authored by Femmy Carrena, at the Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library in Abeokuta, Ogun State capital. Obasanjo said, “My prayer is that all of us will have something to contribute to making this country what God has created it to be – a land flowing with milk and honey.   “We must change the narrative, we must talk to ourselves in the civilised language. “There is nowhere you go in this country that you will not see geniuses in any section of the country. So, why should we look down on ourselves?”  Source By Nse Anthony-Uko (Sundiata Post) – Former President Olusegun Obasanjo has again President Muhammadu Buhari for bringing hardship on Nigerians, saying he has failed Nigerians. Obasanjo on Monday called on President Muhammadu Buhari to stop giving Nigerians excuses, adding that the attitude was why he had not achieved results. The… In "Top Stories" Obasanjo Gives Condition for Supporting Presidential Candidate A former President, Olusegun Obasanjo, has given condition for support any presidential candidate for 2019 general election.   Chief Obasanjo made this known on Thursday while playing host to a presidential aspirant, Kabiru Turaki, at the his residence located inside the Olusegun Obasanjo… In "News" By Bolaji Buhari Lagos -  Former President Olusegun Obasanjo on Saturday met with leaders of the Yoruba socio-cultural group, Afenifere, and other political leaders in the South West on the way forward for Nigeria. The meeting is also about sustaining the unity in Nigeria. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN)… In "Top Stories"